    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix resource block allocation violation in set_dl_DataToUL_ACK function\n\n### Summary\nThe `set_dl_DataToUL_ACK` function in nr_rrc_config.c was setting invalid K1 values for PDSCH-to-HARQ feedback timing, causing resource allocation violations downstream in the scheduler. This fix ensures all values meet the minimum feedback time constraint.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/nr_rrc_config.c`: Modified the `set_dl_DataToUL_ACK` function to properly set K1 values that respect the `DURATION_RX_TO_TX` constraint (must be > 4) and are properly spaced to avoid resource conflicts.\n\n### Reproduction\nWithout this fix, when running NR gNB with UEs that require PUCCH-based HARQ-ACK feedback, you may observe:\n- Assertion failures in the scheduler with messages like \"dl_DataToUL_ACK shouldn't be null here\"\n- Incorrect PDSCH-to-HARQ feedback timing causing retransmission timeouts\n- Resource allocation failures in uplink scheduling\n\nThe issue manifests most clearly when `minRXTXTIME` is set to a value less than 4 in the gNB configuration, or when specific subcarrier spacing configurations are used that require precise K1 timing values.\n"
}